lead_paragraph: The food company H. J. Heinz said first-quarter revenue rose 1.6 percent as sales in developing markets soared. It also said reductions in ketchup prices at Wal-Mart Stores helped demand.

headline.main: Overseas Growth Helps Lift Revenue at Heinz
